7e1c754d-9995-421e-8fdf-963070d943e2.0dd9f127-bc8d-49a0-86e4-160688c353dc.description=Iterates through a list of values.If the list changes while running, the updates will be appended to the list. Inputs\: list - The list to iterate through. separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the list. Returns\: The current element of the list, if the response is has more Responses\: has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned. has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list. failure - failed to process the list. Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously. WARNING\: Any step that will use the results of this Iterator operation will, by default, attempt to assign that step's inputs from a flow variable. If this is left checked, then the first element of the iterator will be used for every cycle of iteration.. 7e1c754d-9995-421e-8fdf-963070d943e2.14766e08-18b9-4ed0-87cb-dc7bddbde219.description=

Responses\:
success - the expression was evaluated.
failure - the expression could not be evaluated.

Returns\: the value of the expression.

Calculates the average usage across all disks in a host.
WMI query does not work in Windows 2000, Windows NT 4.0, and Windows Me/98/95.

Inputs\:
host - the host to measure disk usage on.
username - username for host.
password - password for username.

Responses\:
success - the operation completed.
failure - something went wrong.

Returns\:
the average disk usage.

7e1c754d-9995-421e-8fdf-963070d943e2.fa289a46-c9ce-407d-9b78-925a1dfdffe9.description=
Getting file system list, and free space quantities.
WMI query does not work in Windows 2000, Windows NT 4.0, and Windows Me/98/95.
flow.name: Get Average Disk Usage

staticBinding.value: Select Name, FreeSpace, Size, VolumeDirty from Win32_LogicalDisk where DriveType = 3
